Lake Command Agent Deployment Plan (V1)
Mission

Deploy a modular agent architecture where each agent has one responsibility and communicates through the Lake Command framework. Agents never duplicate work. Each publishes structured data into a central intelligence database that powers maps, forecasts, captain logs, and recommendations.
Core Principles

    One agent = one job.
    All agents report through Lake Command.
    Every observation receives:
        Timestamp
        GPS coordinates
        Confidence score
        Source
        Species (if applicable)

Data is never discarded. Older information decays in confidence rather than being deleted.
Agent 1 — Environmental Collector

Purpose: Continuously gather environmental conditions.

Collects:

    Wind
    Wave height
    Surface temperature
    Thermocline
    Water level
    Barometric pressure
    Moon phase
    Sunrise/Sunset

Publishes: Environmental snapshots.
Agent 2 — Fish Intelligence Agent

Purpose: Estimate fish location and movement.

Inputs:

    Historical catches
    Current weather
    Water temperature
    Structure
    Seasonal migrations

Outputs:

    Probability heat maps
    Active depth ranges
    Migration trends

Agent 3 — Bait Intelligence Agent

Purpose: Track prey movement.

Collects:

    Alewife observations
    Smelt reports
    Goby locations
    Plankton conditions
    Insect hatches

Produces: Likely predator feeding zones.
Agent 4 — Captain Report Parser

Purpose: Read fishing reports and convert them into structured intelligence.

Sources:

    Captain logs
    User reports
    Tournament reports

Extracts:

    Species
    Depth
    Speed
    Lure
    Color
    Time
    GPS (when available)
    Water conditions

Agent 5 — Lure Intelligence Agent

Purpose: Learn what presentations work under specific conditions.

Tracks:

    Lure
    Color
    Speed
    Lead length
    Diver settings
    Success rate

Produces: Ranked lure recommendations by conditions.
Agent 6 — Prediction Engine

Purpose: Combine all collected intelligence.

Produces:

    Bite forecasts
    Confidence scores
    Recommended launch locations
    Best fishing windows
    Suggested depths
    Suggested presentations

Agent 7 — Map Intelligence Agent

Purpose: Render information visually.

Displays:

    Heat maps
    Catch clusters
    Environmental overlays
    Bait movement
    Fish movement
    Weather overlays

Agent 8 — Learning Agent

Purpose: Evaluate prediction accuracy.

Tasks:

    Compare predictions to actual catches
    Adjust weighting
    Improve confidence scoring
    Detect seasonal trends
    Takes all users input data from captain logs and catch reports and compiles data and feeds it back to a central ai manageror server to push it to other users which isnt operational yet

This agent continuously improves the system without changing historical records.
Communication Model

Every agent communicates through the Lake Command event bus.

Example Flow:

Environmental Agent ↓ Fish Intelligence ↓ Prediction Engine ↓ Map Intelligence ↓ Mobile App

Captain reports and lure data feed into the same pipeline to continually refine predictions.
Deployment Order

Phase 1

    Environmental Collector
    Captain Report Parser
    Database

Phase 2

    Fish Intelligence
    Map Intelligence

Phase 3

    Lure Intelligence
    Prediction Engine

Phase 4

    Learning Agent
    Automation
    Continuous optimization

Long-Term Vision

Lake Command becomes an always-running lake intelligence platform. Each agent contributes specialized knowledge, while the Prediction Engine fuses all available information into a single, evolving understanding of lake conditions and fish behavior.